<section id="get-started">
    <div class="container grid-2">
        <div>
            <span class="system-label">DEPLOY.SELF_HOST</span>
            <h2 class="section-heading mb-32">Run it on your hardware.</h2>
            <p class="subhead mb-32">
                One command. Any Linux machine with KVM. Downloads pre-built binaries, a kernel, and an Ubuntu 24.04 rootfs. No Docker, no containers, no orchestration layer.
            </p>

            <div class="anti-pitch">
                <h4>Requirements</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Linux (x86_64 or ARM64)</li>
                    <li>Hardware virtualization (/dev/kvm)</li>
                    <li>Root access for daemon (Firecracker requirement)</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-xs text-muted" style="margin-top: 16px;">
                    Tested on: Raspberry Pi 5, Hetzner AX-series, AWS Graviton metal.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div class="code-panel">
                <pre class="code-panel-pre"><code class="mono"><span class="comment"># 1. Install on your server</span>
<span class="cmd">$ curl -fsSL bhatti.sh/install | sudo bash</span>
<span class="comment">==> Installing bhatti (server, minimal tier)</span>
<span class="comment">    ✓ Firecracker 1.15.0</span>
<span class="comment">    ✓ kernel, rootfs, lohar</span>
<span class="comment">    Admin API key: bht_abc123...</span>

<span class="comment"># 2. Start the daemon</span>
<span class="cmd">$ sudo bhatti serve</span>
<span class="comment">[INFO] Listening on :8080</span>

<span class="comment"># 3. Create a user (API key shown once)</span>
<span class="cmd">$ sudo bhatti user create --name alice</span>
<span class="comment">bht_live_abc123def456...</span>

<span class="comment"># 4. Install CLI on your laptop</span>
<span class="cmd">$ curl -fsSL bhatti.sh/install | bash</span>
<span class="cmd">$ bhatti setup</span>
<span class="comment">API endpoint: https://your-server:8080</span>
<span class="comment">API key: ****</span>
<span class="comment">Testing connection... ✓ connected</span></code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

